pageContext.claim: “Then you have Dianne Feinstein. Dianne Feinstein. Right? Todd Young's friend. Senator Cornyn of Texas looked at her, said, did you leak? And she got scared. You know, he's a pretty tough guy, right, Tom? Really, I mean, this was unbelievable. Did you leak? Senator Cornyn, did you leak? And she goes, uh, what? Did you leak? Did we leak? We went through this. The worst body language any human being has ever used or seen. In other words, she leaked. She leaked. And that's just the beginning.”
pageContext.analysis: There is no evidence that Sen. Dianne Feinstein leaked the letter accusing Supreme Court nominee Brett Kavanaugh of sexual misconduct. Feinstein emphatically denied she had leaked.
